				\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
				\begin{document}$$ \left( {\alpha hv} \right)^{m} = A\left( {hv - E_{g} } \right) $$\end{document}
where, m takes a value of 2 for direct and ½ for indirect band gap, A is a proportional constant, hv is the incident photon energy, α is the absorption coefficient and Eg is the optical band gap. Here, the absorption coefficient α is directly related to the transmittance, reflectance and the thickness of the deposited thin films. The absorption coefficient (αhν) can be evaluated from the following relationship:2α=1dIn1-RT\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
